[SN]TITLE[SN]
University of Sheffield shark study may help humans re-grow teeth

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Research into the way sharks are able to regenerate teeth throughout their lives could be used to help fight tooth loss in humans.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
17 February 2016 Last updated at 19:10 GMT
Scientists at the University of Sheffield have identified the genes, which also present in humans, that sharks use to develop and replace teeth.
It is believed the study could help to develop therapies that might overcome tooth loss.
